Package ru.nsu.fit.oop.veber

Class AdjList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.nsu.fit.oop.veber.AdjList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - elem that can be in vertex (vertexes can be associated with any type)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Graph<T>
    public class AdjList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Graph<T>
    That class implements graph interface and all of its methods. Main idea - that for every element we store set of adjacency vertexes in hashmap. This class must not be used for multi graphs (you must not put multiple edges and loops).

      • addVertex

        public boolean addVertex​(Vertex<T> vertex)
        Method creates new set and adds all incident vertexes to this set. After it, method creates new row to associate vertex with this set. This method does not add vertex, that is already in graph. If vertexes connected to vertex, that are not in graph, we also add those vertexes.
        Specified by:
        addVertex in interface Graph<T>
        Parameters:
        vertex - - vertex that we add to graph
        Returns:
        true - vertex was added, false - vertex was not added
